  + [navigation_graph] is the browsable network of source, subject, narrative, hypergraph, queue, capture, and gate links
  + [sub_agent_cli_layer] is shown as gated worker candidates, launches elsewhere, captured returns, and validation records
  + [wisdom_register] is the interface gives the attention operating system an inspectable cockpit where Codex and user can see what the worker layer is doing before accepting action or integration
  + [caution_register] is interface affordances must not become hidden launch authority, repo mutation authority, stale cache authority, or proof by visual graph
  + [balance_register] is stable because browsing, queue display, capture display, gate display, and action authority remain distinct
  + [utility_horizon] is static read-only browser prototype, job-node view model, narrative timeline renderer, subject link navigator, capture review panel, and authority dashboard
  + [next_step] is keep Task_161 ready or later define a read-only static browser prototype before any interactive runner
  + [outside] is direct mutation, hidden launch, credentials, unbounded worker spawning, stale UI cache, public network bind, and automatic remote publication

  = must: keep first interface prototype read-only or read-first
  = must: expose gates before action controls
  = should: build the view model before building UI code

